                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <head>282. Briefing Note for the December 20 <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                        Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d282fn1">Source: <gloss
                            target="#t_NASA_1">NASA</gloss> space programs. Confidential. 1 p.
                        Eisenhower Library, Whitman File, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                        Records.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1960-12-19">December 19, 1960</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d282-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d282-1"/>
                <p>The first part of the [illegible in the original] item is a report by <gloss
                        target="#t_NASA_1">NASA</gloss> on its outer space programs.</p>
                <p>At the meeting on November 7, 1960, the Council heard a presentation by
                    [illegible in the original] on the outer space programs being <pb facs="1299"
                        n="1194" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_1194"/> conducted under Defense auspices,
                    [illegible in the original] that meeting that the President requested <gloss
                        target="#t_NASA_1">NASA</gloss> to present to the Council a report (a) on
                    the outer space programs now being conducted under the auspices of <gloss
                        target="#t_NASA_1">NASA</gloss>, and (b) on the level of effort the United
                    States should devote to non-military outer space activities in the future.</p>
                <p>(CALL ON: DR. [illegible in the original])</p>
                <p>The second part of the first item is a presentation by Dr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_KGB_1">Kistiakowsky</persName> of a report by the Science
                    Advisory Committee on “Man in Space.”</p>
                <p>(CALL ON: DR. KISTIAKOWSKY)</p>
            </div>
